Also in September American International Group (AIG) required a federal bailout because it had been excessively selling CDS protection without [hedging](../Financial%20Markets/Fixed%20Income%20Securities%20Tools%20for%20Today's%20Markets/Chapter%205/Key%20Rates%20O1s%20Durations%20and%20Hedging.md) against the possibility that the reference entities might decline in value, which exposed the insurance giant to potential losses over $\$100$ billion. The CDS on Lehman were settled smoothly, as was largely the case for the other 11 credit events occurring in 2008 which trggered payouts.55] And while it is arguable that other incidents would have been as bad or worse if less efficient instruments than CDS had been used for [speculation and insurance](Derivatives/Part%20IV%20-%20Options/Chapter%2014%20-%20Options%20Markets.md) purposes, the closing months of 2008 saw regulators working hard to reduce the risk involved in CDS transactions.  

